#!/usr/bin/env bash
# Stop hook: nudge Claude through a single finishing pass before stopping

set -euo pipefail

cat >/dev/null  # drain the hook payload off stdin; the guard works from git state alone
PORCELAIN=$(claude-changeset-guard finish) || exit 0

MESSAGE="You made these changes this session:

$PORCELAIN

Before stopping, do a finishing pass on this change-set. Work through these in order,
keeping each scoped to the change you already made (don't start new work or expand
scope):

1. Consistency: update anything the change-set requires to stay in sync, e.g. CLAUDE.md,
   docs, changelogs, justfile recipes, or code comments.
2. Verify: confirm your changes work, e.g. by building, type-checking, and running tests.

Fix what genuinely needs fixing; if a step has nothing to do, move on. When the diff is
consistent and passes, change nothing and stop."

jq -n --arg ctx "$MESSAGE" '{"systemMessage":"[claude-stop-finish] finishing pass triggered","hookSpecificOutput":{"hookEventName":"Stop","additionalContext":$ctx}}'
exit 0
